Answer:

```java
Map<String, Integer> freq = new HashMap<String, Integer>();
String word = "yourWord";
Integer count = freq.get(word);
if (count == null) {
    freq.put(word, 1);
} else {
    freq.put(word, count + 1);
}
```

In this code, we are using a HashMap to count the frequency of words. The `get` method of the Map is used to get the current count of the word. If the word is not in the map, we put it in with a count of 1. If the word is already in the map, we increment its count by 1.

